<h1>Signaling</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Send and receive a message in the International Morse Code, by buzzer or other sound device at a rate of at least five words per minute.<p>

<li>Show your ability to send and receive a message in the International Morse Code by wigwag, blinker or other light-signaling device at the rate of at least five words per minute.<p>

<li>Know the proper application of the International Morse Code - when, where, and how it can be used to best advantage.<p>

<li>Describe briefly various other codes and methods of signaling which are in common use.<p>

<li>Within a period of three months, log 15 radio contacts showing details of date, time, call sign, signal strength, readability, and location.<p>

<li>Tell in discussion with our Merit Badge Counselor your experience in Radio Scouting communication, as to:
<ol type=a>
<li>Rules and regulations affecting radio communications
<li>Nature of Radio Scouting communication both in local and foreign contacts
<li>Fundamental theories involved in the operation of a radio transceiver</ol></ol>



</span><p>
